stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> WAIT_START
    WAIT_START --> WAIT_START: ruido distinto de @
    WAIT_START --> READ_LEN_HI: @
    READ_LEN_HI --> READ_LEN_LO: hex
    READ_LEN_LO --> EXPECT_LEN_SEPARATOR: hex y 4 <= LL <= MAX
    EXPECT_LEN_SEPARATOR --> READ_BODY: :
    READ_BODY --> READ_BODY: byte imprimible, no @ y body < LL
    READ_BODY --> EXPECT_CHECK_SEPARATOR: se recibieron LL bytes
    EXPECT_CHECK_SEPARATOR --> READ_CHECK_HI: :
    READ_CHECK_HI --> READ_CHECK_LO: hex
    READ_CHECK_LO --> EXPECT_END: hex
    EXPECT_END --> EXPECT_END: CR opcional
    EXPECT_END --> VALIDATE: LF
    VALIDATE --> WAIT_START: CC y TTT:PAYLOAD válidos / MESSAGE_READY
    VALIDATE --> WAIT_START: CC o body inválidos / ERROR

    READ_LEN_HI --> ERROR: otro byte
    READ_LEN_LO --> ERROR: otro byte o longitud inválida
    EXPECT_LEN_SEPARATOR --> ERROR: distinto de :
    READ_BODY --> ERROR: byte no permitido o desborde
    EXPECT_CHECK_SEPARATOR --> ERROR: distinto de :
    READ_CHECK_HI --> ERROR: no hexadecimal
    READ_CHECK_LO --> ERROR: no hexadecimal
    EXPECT_END --> ERROR: distinto de LF o CR
    ERROR --> READ_LEN_HI: byte causante es @ (resincroniza)
    ERROR --> WAIT_START: otro byte
